# Tailwind CSS 4

Project uses Tailwind v4 with **CSS-first configuration**. There is no `tailwind.config.js` — tokens and customization live in CSS via `@theme`.

## Entry CSS

```css
/* apps/web/src/styles/tailwind.css (or wherever it's imported) */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-brand-gold: oklch(0.78 0.10 80);
  --color-brand-ink: #1a1a1a;
  --spacing-128: 32rem;
  --font-serif: "Cormorant Garamond", serif;
}
```

- Replace v3's `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;` with a single `@import "tailwindcss";`.
- Define design tokens as CSS variables under `@theme` using namespaced names (`--color-*`, `--font-*`, `--spacing-*`, `--radius-*`, `--breakpoint-*`, `--shadow-*`).
- Tokens defined under `@theme` become utilities automatically: `--color-brand-gold` → `bg-brand-gold`, `text-brand-gold`, etc.

## PostCSS / Plugin

- Use `@tailwindcss/postcss` (already in deps). Do not pull in the legacy `tailwindcss` core package as a PostCSS plugin.
- Content paths are auto-detected; no `content: [...]` config required.

## Theme Customization

- Extend tokens: just add CSS variables under `@theme`.
- Override tokens: redefine the variable inside a selector (e.g. `:root`, `.dark`, `[data-theme="x"]`).
- Reference tokens in arbitrary CSS via `var(--color-brand-gold)`.

## Dark Mode / Theming

Use a CSS-driven approach (works well with `next-themes`):

```css
@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));
```

Then `dark:bg-brand-ink` etc. work as expected.

## Class Composition

- Use the `cn()` helper (clsx + tailwind-merge) from `src/shared/lib` to merge classes safely:

```tsx
<div className={cn("rounded-md p-4", isActive && "bg-brand-gold", className)} />
```

- Use `class-variance-authority` (cva) for component variants — see the shadcn-ui rule.

## Anti-Patterns

- ❌ Do NOT recreate a `tailwind.config.ts/js` for v4. Use `@theme` in CSS.
- ❌ Do NOT use `@apply` to build complex components — compose with `cn()` instead. Reserve `@apply` for very small primitives.
- ❌ Do NOT hardcode colors when a token exists. Add a token to `@theme` if one is missing.
